Behavior                              Input       Output

Word starts with a vowel (a,e,i,o,u),  "air"       "airay"
add "ay" to the end

Word starts with a single consonant    "hot"       "othay"
(including y), move to the end &
add "ay"

Word starts with multiple consonants   "sweet"     "eetsway"
(including y), move all consonants to
the end & add "ay"

1st or 2nd consonant is (including y)  "squawk"    "awksquay"
"qu", move all consonants and "u" to
the end & add "ay"

Script will run through entire   "old bird yawns" "olday irdbay awnsyay"
sentence, not just one word
